Geode Capital Management LLC Has $25.16 Million Stake in Acadia Realty Trust (AKR)

					Posted by Danessa Lincoln on Jul 27th, 2017 // No Comments 




Geode Capital Management LLC increased its position in shares of  Acadia Realty Trust (NYSE:AKR) by 13.5% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund owned 837,113 shares of the real estate investment trust’s stock after buying an additional 99,395 shares during the period. Geode Capital Management LLC’s holdings in Acadia Realty Trust were worth $25,163,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Other large investors also recently modified their holdings of the company. Vanguard Group Inc. increased its stake in shares of  Acadia Realty Trust by 3.6% in the first quarter. Vanguard Group Inc. now owns 13,251,912 shares of the real estate investment trust’s stock worth $398,353,000 after buying an additional 455,193 shares during the period.  Thrivent Financial For Lutherans increased its stake in shares of  Acadia Realty Trust by 4.6% in the first quarter. Thrivent Financial For Lutherans now owns 96,518 shares of the real estate investment trust’s stock worth $2,901,000 after buying an additional 4,250 shares during the period.  Teacher Retirement System of Texas increased its stake in shares of  Acadia Realty Trust by 2,361.9% in the first quarter. Teacher Retirement System of Texas now owns 161,969 shares of the real estate investment trust’s stock worth $4,869,000 after buying an additional 155,390 shares during the period.  Legal & General Group Plc increased its stake in shares of  Acadia Realty Trust by 13.8% in the first quarter. Legal & General Group Plc now owns 588,229 shares of the real estate investment trust’s stock worth $17,682,000 after buying an additional 71,456 shares during the period.  Finally, Teachers Advisors LLC boosted its position in  Acadia Realty Trust by 5.3% in the first quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC now owns 127,030 shares of the real estate investment trust’s stock worth $3,819,000 after buying an additional 6,399 shares in the last quarter. 


 Get Acadia Realty Trust alerts:



Shares of Acadia Realty Trust (NYSE AKR) opened at 29.63 on Thursday. The company has a market cap of $2.51 billion, a PE ratio of 41.15 and a beta of 0.58. Acadia Realty Trust has a 12 month low of $26.70 and a 12 month high of $37.98. The firm’s 50-day moving average price is $28.08 and its 200 day moving average price is $29.79. 




Acadia Realty Trust (NYSE:AKR) last issued its earnings results on Tuesday, July 25th. The real estate investment trust reported $0.37 EPS for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.08 by $0.29. Acadia Realty Trust had a net margin of 27.19% and a return on equity of 2.92%. The business had revenue of $59.50 million for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $53.72 million. During the same quarter last year, the firm posted $0.37 EPS. The business’s revenue for the quarter was up 35.2% compared to the same quarter last year.  Equities research analysts anticipate that  Acadia Realty Trust will post $0.40 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The firm also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Friday, July 14th. Stockholders of record on Friday, June 30th were paid a $0.26 dividend. This represents a $1.04 dividend on an annualized basis and a dividend yield of 3.51%. The ex-dividend date  was Wednesday, June 28th. Acadia Realty Trust’s dividend payout ratio  is presently 140.54%. 
